                     <title key="work_13618" type="desc">Old Testament, metrical paraphrase</title>
                     <note>Including Judith and the Maccabees; 18,372 lines in 12-line
                        stanzas</note>
                     <note>The books taken are the Pentateuch, Joshua (fol. 25), Judges, Ruth, 1 and 2 Sam. (fol. 44), 1 and 2 Kings, Job (fol. 129v), Tobit, Esther, and Judith. At fol. 162v follow two poems from Maccabees, 'De matre cum vij filijs' and 'De Anthioco' (Antiochus, fol. 167) </note>
                     <incipit>God fader in heuyn of myghtes most That mad this mold &amp; all man
                        kynd</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl><ref target="https://www.dimev.net/record.php?recID=1553">DIMEV
                              1553</ref></bibl>
                     </listBibl>

